<item>
            <title>[LU-10629] Cannot clear a default OST pool from root</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-10629</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If I set a pool to a directory, it does not seem possible to actually remove it.  It can be changed, but a pool cannot be reset to the default.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Things that don&apos;t work:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;lfs setstripe -d /mnt/lustre&lt;br/&gt;
lfs setstripe -p &quot;&quot; /mnt/lustre&lt;br/&gt;
lfs setstripe -p /mnt/lustre&lt;br/&gt;
lfs setstripe -p NONE /mnt/lustre&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I see no other hints in the code as to what it might be.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
